        <h2 style="font-size:medium;font-weight: bold;font-size: larger">How to Login in the system or application?<br></h2>
        <p style="font-weight:500;font-size: large"><em style=";font-weight: bold">Answer:</em><br>For Login first you have to sign up into the application in the sign up page(Which is at the left corner). For sign up you need to provide all the information correctly and also set your password correctly. After filling the form details correctly,do not forget to check the uncheck box which tells that you are agreed with all the terms and conditions for the registration. 
            Then lastly click on the Register button so that your details are registered. After registration you will receive a mail in your provided Email-Id for the final step of validation and registration. Then you can finally login into web application providing your user-id and password which you have set. <br>
        <h4 style="font-weight: bolder">NOTE:Please provide a valid Email-Id.</h4>  </p><br>
    
         <h2 style="font-size:medium;font-weight: bold;font-size: larger">Will the user or patient receive the confirmation message, after making an appointment?<br></h2>
            <p style="font-weight: 500;font-size: large"><em style=";font-weight: bold">Answer:</em><br>Yes, the patient will receive the confirmation about the appointment via email, specifying the details about appointment time, location,date, day and the Doctor chosen.</p><br>
         
         <h2 style="font-size:medium;font-weight: bold;font-size: larger">What happens if two user or patient choose the same appointment at the same time?<br></h2>
            <p style="font-weight: 500;font-size: large"><em style=";font-weight: bold">Answer:</em><br>The first patient to select the appointment will be allocated with the space. The second patient to select the appointment will be advised that the appointment is no longer available, and to choose chose another appointment time.   </p><br>
            
            <h2 style="font-size:medium;font-weight: bold;font-size: larger">  What should I do if I miss my appointment?<br></h2>
            <p style="font-weight: 500;font-size: large"><em style=";font-weight: bold">Answer:</em><br>We ask that you call our office during regular office hours (8 AM - 5 PM Monday to Saturday) and explain that you have missed your appointment and discuss rescheduling the appointment. 
                 Please keep in mind that this will appear as a No Show appointment unless notification occurs within 2 hours prior to your appointment.</p><br>
            
            
            
            <h2 style="font-size:medium;font-weight: bold;font-size: larger">What medical information should I bring with me?<br></h2>
            <p style="font-weight: 500;font-size: large"><em style=";font-weight: bold">Answer:</em><br>Be sure to bring a complete list of the medications and dosages you currently are taking (Your doctor also may ask to see your medications, so please have them available.).
                If possible, please bring a letter from your local doctor summarizing your medical condition.
                Copies of your medical record, including pertinent X-rays and other test results related to your current medical concerns also will be helpful. 
                Please be aware, however, that Stay Healthy Hospital's doctors may find it necessary to repeat some of these tests to ensure the most accurate diagnosis possible.</p><br>
            
            
            
            <h2 style="font-size:medium;font-weight: bold;font-size: larger">How much time will my medical evaluation require?<br></h2>
            <p style="font-weight: 500;font-size: large"><em style=";font-weight: bold">Answer:</em><br>The time required for a medical evaluation depends on your medical needs. 
                Medical evaluations usually can be completed within three to six working days; however, additional testing or consultations may require more time. 
                In some instances, your evaluation or treatment may require a return visit.
                We encourage you to keep your travel plans as flexible as possible. 
                Please note that Stay Healthy Hospital is not open on weekends or holidays.</p><br>
            
            
             <h2 style="font-size:medium;font-weight: bold;font-size: larger">How do I get a refill on my prescription?<br></h2>
             <p style="font-weight: 500;font-size: large"><em style=";font-weight: bold">Answer:</em><br>We ask that prescription refills be completed during regular office visits whenever possible.
                 Calls for prescription refills may be made 24 hours a day through our phone tree.
                 Physicians must have the benefit of reviewing your medical record before prescribing any additional medications.
                 Calculate in advance when you may need a refill on medicines that were prescribed by us, as we require at least 72 hours notice. Please allow at least 7 days to refill narcotics. 
                 Please have the medication name and dose, pharmacy name and number available, and leave your name and date of birth and attending physician, so we may expedite your request.
                 Certain prescriptions must be picked up and signed for during regular office hours.</p>
            
     
    
   
